HEADWORD: Louping
<hw>Loup"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Loup</er> to
leap.]</ety> <fld>(Veter.)</fld> <def>An enzo⟦oum⟧tic, often fatal,
disease of sheep and other domestic animals, of unknown cause. It is
characterized by muscular tremors and spasms, followed by more or less
complete paralysis. The principal lesion is an inflammation of the
membranes covering the brain and spinal cord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loup-loup</ent>⟦br⟧
